message.content: It is not possible to provide an accurate summary of what most women in Western Sahara think of divorce as opinions on this matter can vary greatly among individuals. Women's perspectives on divorce in Western Sahara, as in any society, are influenced by various factors such as cultural, religious, and personal beliefs. Some women may view divorce as a necessary option to escape abusive or unhappy marriages, while others may prioritize maintaining the stability of their families and may be more hesitant to consider divorce. It is important to recognize that women's opinions on divorce are diverse and can differ significantly based on their individual experiences and circumstances.
